- Firewalls are added to restrict access to servers, ensuring only authorized traffic is allowed. They act as a security barrier.
- SSL/TLS (HTTPS) is used to secure traffic between clients and the web servers, ensuring data confidentiality and integrity.
- Monitoring is used to detect issues, analyze performance, and provide insights for optimization.
- Monitoring Tools collect data by deploying monitoring clients on web and application servers, capturing logs and metrics.


Issues

- terminating SSL at the  doesn't provide end-to-end encryption. Sensitive data is decrypted at the load balancer, potentially exposing it to internal threats.

- If the MySQL server fails it can lead to data loss or downtime.

- Using identical components across servers may lead to a single point of failure affecting all servers.